This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with speech recognition and language modeling. It may also fall under "Sound" (cs.SD) as it involves acoustic modeling. Additionally, it could be categorized under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it discusses neural networks and their training. "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) are also possible categories as the paper deals with language processing and recognition.
